reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks so good!
reviews.reviewText: Pros:The rgb looks goodVery sturdyMetalCan daisychain with other argb componentsCons:Cable was too short to go through the bottom grommet and run behind my motherboard to the argb 5v header.To get around the con I had to run the cable up the middle of my board and conceal it under my aio tubes and by my ram. But it looks good and definitely would recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quality support, easy to install and looks great
reviews.reviewText: Great GPU brace. RGB looks tasteful and install was easy. Note that you do not need to have 3 free slots in order to install. I installed it using only 2 slots and it's perfectly stable and secure for my 4080.Only con is that it comes with absolutely no documentation. But a quick google search will give you what you need, if you need it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Fits but with alot of bending and adjustments!
reviews.reviewText: Depending on the height of your card, you may have to bend the brace downward towards the GPU. It hold up a 3080 ti pretty well, although the brace itself sags from the weight. Though this isnt completely the fault of the brace considering my card has sloping edges which BTW, I was dumb with the rubber feet, installing them horizontally instead of vetically which would just make it slip out of place.Overall, good quality for the most part but doesnt work out of box, as mentioned before and if you see other peoples photos, the brace has to be bent down towards GPU if the card height is lower.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Does what it says at a great price
reviews.reviewText: I almost bought a not RGB bracket for like $3 less, but bought this one, figuring with my recent RGB addiction, that Id risk a couple bucks and give it a shot. It genuinely impressed me, the LEDs aren't perfectly blended like an ultra premium product, but the lighting array is pretty dang smooth, especially the sub $15 price point, I feel like I got something I would have been willing to pay $40 for. And for those that don't care about the lights and just need a bracket for gpu support, it does great. I have a heavy Zotac 3090, and it holds it up great. If you have a heavy GPU like mine, I wild recommend while the PC is on its side, load it so that the GPU looks slightly pushed toward the CPU, and then when it's vertical and it's taking the weight, it will be horizontal

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect GPU Support Stand
reviews.reviewText: I like how easy it was to install into my pc and the rgb’s work perfect and fit my system great! Very pleasing for my all white build and provides great support for my gpu!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars EVGA rtx card owners beware
reviews.reviewText: It works but it there’s a few things to keep in mind before you purchase this: If you have an evga rtx card you are going to have a hard time. I have a 3080 ftw3 and I had to bend the bracket towards me for it to have something to push of. The evga shroud does not cover the fans. They are fully exposed. If you installed this without bending it you wouldn’t be able to place the stand anywhere. It does work but it wouldn’t be lined up to my card. It looks good, it’s solid metal and the lights work. I’m going to keep mine simply because all other brackets are similarly designed and the gpu itself doesn’t lend well to this kind of support.Update: I got it to work but moving the little holder bracket near one of the plastic dividers on the fans. I used both pads and put them in the middle and just adjusted them until they supported the card. Be very careful though as any kind of movement on the computer and the support could budge and send it straight into the fan.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on October 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: The UpHere! GPU sag support is good for the price.
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Bought this for my RTX 2080Ti as it was starting to sag due to the weight of it. First off the logo on mine was all scrambled up for some reason but I'll just stick a Geforce RTX decal over it, the support itself is pretty sturdy though, and seems well made, at first though I wasn't sure it was going to support the card because my PC was on its side and the arm seemed to slip out of place slightly, but I can happily say once the pc was upright and the weight of the card was bearing down on it, it doesn't move at all. The ARGB lights offer a really nice bit of design to the interior and work well too.

Die upHere RGB LED Grafikkartenstütze ist einfach großartig! Sie erfüllt alle meine Erwartungen und noch mehr. Hier sind einige Gründe, warum ich diese Stütze mit 5 Sternen bewerte:Stabil:Die Stütze ist äußerst stabil und sorgt dafür, dass meine Grafikkarte perfekt in Position bleibt, ohne zu wackeln oder sich zu neigen. Selbst bei intensiven Gaming-Sessions und Vibrationen bleibt meine Grafikkarte sicher und stabil in ihrer Halterung.Schön:Die RGB LED-Beleuchtung dieser Grafikkartenstütze ist absolut atemberaubend. Sie verleiht meinem gesamten PC-Setup eine zusätzliche Dimension und bringt einen Hauch von Eleganz mit sich. Die Farben sind lebendig und die Möglichkeit, sie anzupassen, um sie an meinen persönlichen Stil anzupassen, ist fantastisch.Passt perfekt:Die Grafikkartenstütze passt tatsächlich perfekt zu meiner Grafikkarte und meinem Gehäuse. Die Einstellmöglichkeiten ermöglichen es, sie genau auf die richtige Höhe einzustellen, um eine optimale Unterstützung zu gewährleisten. Es war ein Kinderspiel, sie zu installieren und anzupassen.Insgesamt bin ich von der upHere RGB LED Grafikkartenstütze begeistert. Sie erfüllt nicht nur ihren Zweck, sondern verleiht meinem PC-Setup auch eine erstaunliche Optik. Wenn Sie nach einer stabilen, schönen und perfekt passenden Grafikkartenstütze suchen, dann ist diese definitiv die richtige Wahl!
